 <div class="container">
    <h2>Key Features:</h2>
    <h3>1. Top 10 Websites Overview:</h3>
    <p>Displays a list of the most popular websites globally, based on factors like traffic, engagement, and relevance. Ideal for quick reference to top-performing sites across the web.</p>

    <h3>2. Categories Access:</h3>
    <p>Websites are grouped into relevant categories, making it easy for users to explore the best websites based on their interest. Categories include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>News:</strong> Top news websites providing global and local news coverage.</li>
        <li><strong>E-Commerce:</strong> The leading online shopping platforms.</li>
        <li><strong>Entertainment:</strong> Websites with the best movies, music, and streaming services.</li>
        <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> Popular social networking platforms.</li>
        <li><strong>Technology:</strong> Top websites for tech updates, gadgets, and reviews.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Category-specific Endpoints:</h3>
    <p>Each category has its own API endpoint, allowing users to retrieve the top 10 websites for that specific category. Example: <code>/api/categories/news</code> would return the top 10 news websites.</p>

    <h2>How to Use:</h2>
    <p>To retrieve data, simply send a request to the corresponding API endpoint. For example, to get the top 10 websites in the "E-Commerce" category, use the following request:</p>

    <pre>
GET /api/categories/ecommerce
    </pre>
   <pre class="bg-dark text-white">
fetch('https://websitehub-vki3.onrender.com/api/category') //category need to change website category to need
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(data => console.log(data))
    .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
   </pre>
    <p>To retieve all api-data data </p>
    <pre>
GET /api/
    </pre>
    <pre class="bg-dark text-white">
fetch('https://websitehub-vki3.onrender.com/api/')
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(data => console.log(data))
    .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
    </pre>
    <p>The response will include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Website name</li>
        <li>Website URL</li>
        <li>Brief description of the website</li>
    </ul>

